news.title: China: Kaisa Group's shares fall on ratings downgrade
news.para: Kaisa's shares fell as much as 19.9% to an all-time low of HK$1.17 on Thursday afternoon, while its 11.25% April 2022 bond dropped more than 8 points to trade at less than 35% of its face value, according to data provider Duration Finance.

news.title: Evergrande makes coupon payment before Friday deadline: Sources
news.para: Evergrande, once China's top-selling developer, is reeling under more than $300 billion in liabilities, fuelling worries about the impact of its fate on the world's second-largest economy as well as on global markets.

news.title: CCP to sign leases with tenants of Panaji municipal market complex
news.para: The CCP has identified over 400 such tenants that were operating in the premises rent-free. PIL filed in the high court of Bombay at Goa in July 2017 had given the corporation one year to recover rent/licence fee arrears and initiate action against illegal occupants.

news.title: Over 4,000 buildings are without fire NOC in Gujarat
news.para: For enforcing the installation of fire prevention systems in buildings, the government said that it has taken action against 1,285 hospitals in last three months for not having fire NOC.

news.title: Telangana's Dharani land portal completes 10 lakh transactions
news.para: The web portal was launched on October 29, last year to complete agricultural land registrations, mutations and other land related transactions.

news.title: Rajasthan to move SC against ban on illegal colonies' regularisation
news.para: As the directions have put a spoke in the ambitious six-month special campaign ‘Shahar-2021’on a petition filed by Roshan Vyas, the urban development and housing (UDH) department is gearing up to move SC.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA identifies two plots to develop flats for the poor
news.para: These plots are in sectors 2 and Omicron 1A. The e-auction will take place next month. The construction of one and two-room flats is expected to begin early next year.

news.title: Vastu Housing Finance to raise about $200 million from a consortium of investors
news.para: “With this investment, Vastu will further consolidate operations in 13 states and build products to provide faster and affordable credit for about 900 million population residing in these states,” said Sandeep Menon, Founder, MD & CEO, Vastu Housing Finance.

news.title: Godrej family looks to divide a $4.1 billion empire
news.para: Reorganising the consumer goods to real estate and engineering empire has been under discussion for months and has now gathered momentum with Pirojsha Godrej, Adi Godrej's son, representing that side of the family.

news.title: SC allows new board of Unitech to appoint PMCs for completion of stalled projects
news.para: The top court also took note of the Action Taken Report (ATR) filed by the new board of management about the settlement of claims with Suraksha ARC saying no resolution has been found yet.

news.title: Kone posts operating profit of 326.5 million euros in Q3 2021
news.para: Chief Executive Henrik Ehrnrooth told Reuters semiconductor shortage had got worse after the first half year and said there are now supply difficulties at all points of the logistics chain.

news.title: China builders hit by downgrades as Evergrande deadline looms
news.para: Shares of Kaisa Group were hardest-hit, losing nearly a fifth of their value on Thursday after rating agency downgrades that highlighted the company's limited access to funding and significant U.S. dollar debt obligations.

news.title: Skanska posts profit of $179 million in July-Sept 2021
news.para: CEO Anders Danielsson told Reuters that Skanska's projects had been little delayed by global supply chain bottlenecks, and margins had not been too affected by higher prices for steel, wood products and other building materials.

news.title: Court dismisses bail plea of Ambience Group's promoter in money laundering case
news.para: The ED had raided Gehlot, his company Aman Hospitality Private Limited (AHPL), some other firms of the Ambience group, director in the company Dayanand Singh, Mohan Singh Gehlot, and their associates in July last year.

news.title: Salesforce leases seven lakh sq ft of office space in Hyderabad
news.para: "The lease has a lock-in period of 3 years and commands a rent of Rs 71 per sq ft. The deal was registered earlier this month," mentioned a document shared by Propstack.
